OL,6,F"You have a long history of drug abuse
OL,7,Fand it may well be that your thinking
OL,8,Fwas disturbed to some extent.
OL,9,FDischarging this weapon at someone's
OL,10,Ftemple at close range - you are both
OL,11,Ffortunate that no further harm was
OL,12,Fcaused."
OL,14,FSpeaking to Mr Sharp, who sat in the
OL,15,Fpublic gallery, the judge said that
OL,16,Fthe law does not permit him to suspend
OL,17,Fthe sentence. Richardson, of Telford
OL,18,FClose in Hartlepool, was jailed for 32-
OL,19,Fmonths.
